  <bodyText><![CDATA[<div class="g12"><img src="/media/13054406/treasures-of-austria.jpg" alt="Treasures -of -austria" rel="879,452" /></div>
<div> </div>
<!--start left column-->
<div class="g7">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<p class="p1"><strong>This special trip takes you on an evocative tour of Austria’s musical history and classical highlights, as well as some of the country’s most beautiful scenery. Immerse yourself in the cultural delights of the historic cities of <a data-udi="umb://document/31b86014d3b04c3da584cc56dca63c66" href="/{localLink:umb://document/31b86014d3b04c3da584cc56dca63c66}" title="Salzburg">Salzburg</a>, Graz and <a data-udi="umb://document/d9194f7378c74152b5986f929fcea9ab" href="/{localLink:umb://document/d9194f7378c74152b5986f929fcea9ab}" title="Vienna">Vienna</a>, hop over the Danube into Bratislava, and relax in the picturesque Wachau wine growing region and the tranquil <a data-udi="umb://document/c5e46af3b3f94da5945ec9359b07cfac" href="/{localLink:umb://document/c5e46af3b3f94da5945ec9359b07cfac}" title="The Salzkammergut">Salzkammergut</a> Lake District. En route, enjoy optional classical music concerts, iconic Sound of Music locations, and visit the homes of famous classical composers, Mozart, Haydn and Strauss. Exclusive to Inghams, this tour runs every 4 weeks and you will be looked after along the way by our popular Inghams tour guide, Gary.</strong></p>
</div>
<div> </div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Itinerary</h2>
<p><strong>VISIT Salzburg &amp; ‘Sound of Music’ locations – Melk &amp; Dürnstein – Vienna – Bratislava* – Eisenstadt – Graz – St. Wolfgang</strong></p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>SATURDAY</strong></p>
<p>Fly to Salzburg and transfer to your comfortable 4 Star hotel in central Salzburg (<a data-udi="umb://document/cf77e75ff481422ba6e14839b587ad3c" href="/{localLink:umb://document/cf77e75ff481422ba6e14839b587ad3c}" title="Hotel Salzburger-hof">Hotel Salzburgerhof</a> or similar). Unwind from the day’s travelling and maybe have a stroll around the nearby Mirabell Gardens. Meet your Inghams tour guide to discuss your trip ahead.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>SUNDAY</strong></p>
<p>A morning walking tour around Salzburg’s Old Town (90 mins), followed by time for lunch at leisure in the centre of this romantic city. In the afternoon we take a guided Sound of Music excursion which includes a visit to the unique Hellbrunn Palace (entrance included) and Lake Mondsee, famous for the Sound of Music wedding church. Here you have time for coffee and cake or a stroll along the lakeside before returning to Salzburg. In the evening, join the optional Sound of Salzburg evening tour which includes dinner and a classical music concert (approx €49).</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>MONDAY</strong></p>
<p>Sit back and enjoy the scenery of Upper and Lower Austria as today’s journey takes you to Vienna. En route, the coach stops in the pretty Wachau area, a popular wine-growing region, where a memorable Danube river cruise to Dürnstein awaits you. Have lunch in this beautiful medieval town on the river bank before travelling further east towards Vienna. On arrival in Vienna, enjoy a 1 hour sightseeing coach tour before checking in at the centrally located 4 Star <a data-udi="umb://document/b5f4c64c56ba47158e55297e64432db6" href="/{localLink:umb://document/b5f4c64c56ba47158e55297e64432db6}" title="Hotel Kaiserhof">Hotel Kaiserhof</a> (or similar). For the evening, experience the rustic ambience of a traditional Viennese Heurigen restaurant (dinner and one drink included).</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>TUESDAY</strong></p>
<p>We start the day with a tour of the Schönbrunn Palace. Afterwards explore Vienna further on your own or take the optional excursion to nearby Bratislava, the Slovakian capital on the Danube (approx €30). At night, we highly recommend our optional classical concert at the Kursalon (approx €60).</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>WEDNESDAY</strong></p>
<p>Depart Vienna and visit Eisenstadt and the majestic Esterhazy Palace (entrance included). The famous composer Haydn lived and worked here for over 40 years. Time at leisure for lunch in the historic Old Town (perhaps visit the Haydn museum), before continuing on to the Styrian capital of Graz for 2 nights at the centrally located 4 Star Hotel Das Weitzer (or similar).</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>THURSDAY</strong></p>
<p>A morning walking tour of Graz, a UNESCO world heritage site. Free time to explore the lovely old town with its splendid churches and palaces, in the afternoon the opportunity to join an optional excursion to nearby Piber, home of the famous Lipizzaner white horses that are bred here and supplied to the Spanish riding school in Vienna (approx €20).</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>FRIDAY</strong></p>
<p>On the last day we leave Graz behind and travel back to Salzburg, with a stop in St. Wolfgang in the beautiful Salzkammergut Lake District. Here you can take an optional scenic boat trip on Lake Wolfgang (approx €10) or stroll along the promenade or the narrow cobbled streets in the town centre. Return to Salzburg and we end the tour with a farewell dinner.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>SATURDAY</strong></p>
<p>Depart by coach to Salzburg airport for your flight home or transfer to your chosen resort if you wish to extend your holiday.</p>
<p> </p>
<p style="font-size: 80%;">On some departures it may be necessary to use hotels other than those shown.<br />Our air-conditioned coaches are modern and comfortable and equipped with onboard toilet. Convenient stops will be made en-route at lunch time where snacks or meals can be purchased. Optional excursions are bookable locally, prices are for guidance only.<br />Please note that we act at all times as selling agent for the suppliers of activities &amp; excursions.</p>
</div>
<div> </div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>What’s included</h2>
<ul>
<li>Return flights to Salzburg from the UK<br />• Transfers to/from airport<br />• 4 Star hotel accommodation on bed/breakfast basis: Salzburg (2 nights) - Vienna (2 nights) - Graz (2 nights) - Salzburg (1 night)<br />• Heurigen dinner &amp; farewell dinner<br />• Travel in luxury air-conditioned coaches<br />• Experienced Inghams tour guide<br />• Guided tours, excursions and entrances*<br />*Included except where described as ‘optional</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Optional Extras</strong></p>
<p>• Sound of Salzburg Dinner &amp; Concert (€49)<br />• Kursalon Strauss concert (€60)<br />• Bratislava, Slovakia (€30)<br />• Piber horse stud trip (€20)<br />• Lake Wolfgang boat trip (€10)</p>
<div style="columns: 100px 2; -webkit-columns: 100px 2; /* safari and chrome */-moz-columns: 100px 2;"></div>
</div>
